== Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Cut @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Toss potatoes on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

While veggies roast, cut @Broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Apple{1}.

Halve and toast @Demi-Baguette{1}; halve crosswise and slice into 1-inch pieces.

Place broccoli in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}; cover tightly with @plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender, ~{1-2%minutes}, tossing halfway through. Carefully uncover (watch out for steam!) and toss broccoli with salt and pepper.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

== Fondue ==

Meanwhile, heat @Cream Sauce Base{8%ounce}, @Cheese Roux Concentrate{1%ounce}, and @water{2%TBSP} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat until steaming and slightly bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Use 4 TBSP water if making 4 servings.

Reduce heat to medium. Add @White Cheddar Cheese{1%cup} and @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup} one small handful at a time, alternating and whisking constantly between additions, until melted.

== Assembly ==

Arrange potatoes, carrots, broccoli, apple slices, and baguette pieces on a large #board{} or #platter{}. Serve family style with fondue for dipping.

> Place a trivet or kitchen towel underneath the fondue pot to protect your surface. Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!

Thinly slice beef against the grain; serve alongside fondue board.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.